  • Wireless App Control: Use the Govee Home App to access the Smart Plug via WiFi and Bluetooth to enjoy powerful control and convenient features no matter where you are. Note: Don't support 5G WiFi.
  • Smart Voice Control: Compatible with Alexa and Google Assistant for hands-free on/off control of your plugged-in devices and appliances. Note: Users must create a new Govee Home App account or be logged in to use this Wi-Fi Plug.
  • Compact 2-in-1 Design: With 2 horizontally-positioned plugs, Dual Smart Plug only covers a single outlet in a normal vertical outlet fixture. Which expand your 2-socket fixtures into 4 smart outlets. Each sockets can be controlled independently.
  • Set Automated Timers: Create customized timers and on/off schedules for all your devices and electronic appliances powered by Smart Plug, helping to save on energy and monthly bills.
  • Easy to Set Up: Simply plug in Smart Plug, download the free Govee Home App to your phone, then follow the simple instructions to add the "H5082" Smart Plug. Set up only takes a minute and no other physical hub is required for wireless control.
  • This smart plug is ETL certified, ensuring it meets stringent safety standards for reliable and secure operation.

Product description


Independent or Group Control

The 2 sockets of each Smart Plug can be controlled independently or together. Also create on/off schedules using Govee Home App so your morning toast and coffee are always ready when you wake.


Control with Your Voice

Use simple voice commands to turn on/off all your plugged-in lights, devices, and appliances using Alexa or Google Assistant via WiFi.


Schedules and Timers

Create customized timers and daily schedules to automatically power on/off your electronic appliances, helping save on your monthly power bill. (This function requires manual ON/OFF settings based on the day and hour of the week.)


Group Control Function

Using multiple Smart Plugs, program all your outlets together so all your appliances and devices switch on simultaneously right before you arrive home.


Smart App Control

Easily control all your home appliances powering on/off via WiFi or Bluetooth with the free, intuitive, and expansive Govee Home App.


Compact Design

A compact 2-in-1 horizontal design helps double available outlets without blocking others. Perfect for wireless outlet control and expansion of available sockets.

Simple Setup with Govee Home App

How to Connect with Govee Home App?

  • Plug in Smart Plug
  • Download Govee Home App.
  • Open the app, tap the "+" icon in top right corner, and search "H5082"
  • Tap the device icon and follow the instructions to complete pairing.

Specification

  • Rated Voltage: AC 120V
  • Rated Current: 15A Resistive (Max)
  • AC Frequency: 60Hz
  • Max Total Output Power: 1800W

Note: Users must create a new Govee Home App account or be logged in to use this Wi-Fi Plug.

    • Jaimi
      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Great outlets! Compact for a dual outlet! Simple to set up and very reliable!
      Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2022
      Number of Items: 2
      I've tried nearly a dozen different affordable smart outlet options. Govee smart plugs are very quickly becoming my favorite. I do tend to prefer their single smart plugs though. While I do love the single smart plugs, I also really love these dual smart plugs... See more
      I've tried nearly a dozen different affordable smart outlet options.
      Govee smart plugs are very quickly becoming my favorite. I do tend to prefer their single smart plugs though. While I do love the single smart plugs, I also really love these dual smart plugs since I live in an older house and some rooms don't have many outlets. The dual smart plug acts as a splitter and lets me independently control whatever I plug in. It's incredibly handy and doubles my outlet space in rooms where I'm lucky to have a single outlet normally. Before I got the Govee single smart plugs I was using these on small extension cords in my tropical plant cabinets. They're really nice because they don't overlap other outlets even on small power strips. They are wide though, so it would depend on the orientation of the plugs in your power strip.

      The Govee outlets are some of the easiest smart plugs I've ever set up. I've not come across issues where they don't pair or aren't detectable like I have with other brands. They also seem to reconnect themselves pretty well when my power goes out or if I unplug them. I haven't had to re-pair them or reset them. They work really well with my Amazon Alexa devices AND with the Apple Home features.

      I previously used these specific outlets to automatically control fans and grow lights in my tropical plant cabinets. These plants are really sensitive to changes so having consistent light, heat, humidity, and general conditions are really important. I use a modified Ikea cabinet and I use these Govee outlets with my Amazon Alexa routines to control nearly everything. This also gives me the ability to turn them on or off as needed by just asking Alexa.

      I'm not sure if these outlets are meant for humid environments though. I worked around that by placing a piece of tape over the side buttons and over any unused portion of the outlet. Specifically the ground hole of the plug used for my fans. I haven't had any issues with humidity while doing this. I will also add that because I hide the cables and plugs in my cabinet I'm never using them manually. The tape may mess with the buttons if you're using them manually on a regular basis.

      I also really like Govee in general because they provide affordable options for smart devices. I've had really positive experiences with their Wifi Smart Bulbs, Single Smart Plug, LED light strips, and Flow Plus LED Light Bars. Because of this I'm also considering replacing my current humidifiers and thermometer/hygrometers with the Govee options! The Govee app in general has been incredibly reliable and easy to navigate. It's super simple to connect to other apps and I'm generally a huge fan.

    • alrightalrightalright
      5.0 out of 5 starsVerified Purchase
      Awesome
      Reviewed in the United States on March 6, 2023
      Number of Items: 4
      I recently received an echo show as a gift. This was my first experience with smart products, so I wanted to give its features a try. The first thing I turned to was a few plugs so that I could automatically turn things off when I leave the room or the house. Initially I... See more
      I recently received an echo show as a gift. This was my first experience with smart products, so I wanted to give its features a try. The first thing I turned to was a few plugs so that I could automatically turn things off when I leave the room or the house. Initially I tried a different brand that has great reviews, but as soon as I got them, I realized how awful they were - they were huge, didnt have Bluetooth, and were a pain to connect. Govee to the rescue! These are like a luxury item in comparison to those. The Govee plugs are so easy to set up, the app just works, and has more features than I know what to do with. You can choose how you want to pair them (BT or Wifi), and the process is more or less automatic from there. You can set timers. Oh, and a feature I didnt think I cared about quickly became my favorite one when I remembered how often I need to manually reset my router. With the other plugs, I would still have to get up and go unplug and re-plug everything in. With the Govee, even if WiFi is down it can connect via Bluetooth, so resetting it is just as straightforward as it would be if the WiFi wasnt out. Ive never had an issue with BT range - my phone and echo are probably ~40 feet from the router, through some doors and through a brick wall. Its a small, but welcome convenience that I never want to live without again. Ive had these for about 3 months now, and so far I havent had a single issue. My only complaint is that I wish they tracked power usage. I have a power strip from another brand that does this, and while its not needed, it is nice to know. If I can see where the bulk of my power usage is coming from, then I can be more mindful about what appliances are running and when. All in all, I recommend giving these a shot. I had an issue with another Govee product (I say issue, but really it was a that they didnt fit where I intended to use them), and their customer service was incredibly proactive in reaching out to me and rectifying the problem even though it was well past my return window. I feel good about my purchase and love knowing that if anything were to come up, the Govee team will be there to help.
